\end_inset

), the effects of changes in separation between rich and poor is only implicitly
 stated with constraints on 
\begin_inset Formula $a,b$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta$
\end_inset

.
 In other words, the effect of change in life-standards that define poor
 and rich identities in an economy are exogenous in the model.
 Despite the exogenous treatment, it is worth commenting on how changes
 in the life-standards that define rich or poor status 
